Brandon Pickering
Unix
cs184-abq


To build:
  make


Command line flags:

  --freq|-f N
      For each pixel, supersample using an NxN jittered grid.
      N=0 disables supersampling, and is the default.

  --output|-o file
      Specify output file. By default, sends to stdout.

  --size|-s width height
      Specify the size of the output image. Default is 700x700.

  --structure|-S str
      If str is linear|l, don't use any spatial partitioning.
      If str is bvh, use a bounding volume hierarchy.
      Default is linear.


To render all examples (takes about 4 minutes on instructional machines):
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -o examples/image-01.ppm examples/input-01
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-02.ppm examples/input-02
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-03.ppm examples/input-03
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-04.ppm examples/input-04
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-05.ppm examples/input-05
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-06.ppm examples/input-06
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-07.ppm examples/input-07
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-08.ppm examples/input-08
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-09.ppm examples/input-09
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-10.ppm examples/input-10
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-11.ppm examples/input-11
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-12.ppm examples/input-12
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -f 4 -o examples/image-13.ppm examples/input-13
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -S bvh -f 4 -o examples/image-14.ppm examples/input-14
./as2 -s 1024 1024 -S bvh -f 4 -o examples/image-15.ppm examples/input-15
